Yesterday, senior officials from the White House, Department of Defense, and Department of Homeland Security met for the first Council of Governors meeting under the Biden Administration. The meeting was held to discuss upcoming initiatives and priorities. Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro Mayorkas provided opening remarks, along with the Co-Chairs of the Council of Governors, Governor Mike DeWine of Ohio and Governor Tim Walz of Minnesota. The meeting covered topics such as cybersecurity, disaster preparedness, readiness and response efforts, support for military families, and National Guard initiatives. The Council of Governors was established by President Obama in 2010 as a platform for state and federal officials to address issues related to national security, homeland defense, cybersecurity, disaster response and recovery, military activities, and the National Guard.